  "prompt": "Can a govt employee in india do a part time work?",
  "response": "In India, government employees are generally restricted from engaging in part-time work or additional employment. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Government Service Rules:\n- Most government employees are bound by service rules that prohibit them from taking up additional employment\n- They require prior permission from their department for any secondary work\n\n2. General Restrictions:\n- Cannot engage in private business or commercial activities\n- Cannot accept any part-time or full-time job outside government service\n- Cannot work as a consultant or advisor without official permission\n\n3. Exceptions:\n- Teaching or academic work (with prior approval)\n- Literary, artistic, or scientific work\n- Occasional work that doesn't interfere with official duties\n- Participation in sports or cultural activities\n\n4. Conditions for Permission:\n- Must submit a written request to their department\n- Work should not conflict with official responsibilities\n- No potential conflict of interest\n- No compromise of official duties\n\n5. Consequences of Violation:\n- Disciplinary action\n- Potential suspension\n- Termination of service\n\n6. Recommendations:\n- Always seek formal approval from the department\n- Maintain transparency about additional work\n- Ensure no conflict with primary job responsibilities\n\nNote: Specific rules can vary slightly between different government departments and organizations.",
